\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ This is the wording of Jonathans translation, except that Jonathan renders: Now what does the one 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ seek except seed of God? The explanation is correct except for the fact that the word \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ האחד\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  is pointed 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ with "zakef mark, and the mark of the "zakef separates the word \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ מבקש\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  from joining \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ ומה האחד\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ . It 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ connects it to \lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ זרע א-להים\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ . \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ He had a different spirit\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\  His intention was not like your intention. He did 
\lang1033\ltrch\f0\fs36\b0\i0\ul0\cf0\cb8\ not cast his eye upon her. He had a different intention. They said to him, \lang1033\ltrch\f2\fs36\b\i0\ul0\cf2\cb10\ Now what did the one 
